{"id":41160,"date":"2023-09-08T20:10:42","date_gmt":"2023-09-08T16:10:42","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=41160"},"modified":"2023-09-08T20:31:16","modified_gmt":"2023-09-08T16:31:16","slug":"righteous-wicked-facilitated","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/09\/08\/righteous-wicked-facilitated\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Qadr: Righteous and wicked facilitated for their fate"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hisham ibn Hakim reported: A man came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, shall we start acting or has fate already been decreed?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, Allah Almighty took the progeny of Adam from their backs and made them bear witness against themselves. Then, He announced to them in His palms, saying: These are in Paradise, and these are in Hellfire. Thus, the people of Paradise are facilitated for the deeds of Paradise, and the people of Hellfire are facilitated for the deeds of Hellfire.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Sunnah li-Ibn Abi\u0304 \u2018A\u0304s\u0323im 168<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0647\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u062d\u064e\u0643\u0650\u064a\u0645\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064b\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062a\u064e\u062f\u0650\u0